{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17513225","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17513225"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T13:06:51+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T13:06:51+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12059"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"12059","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/12059"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.11,0.06,0.09,0.06,0.68]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"4626"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78421"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"4626","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4626"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12059"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63783"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"1"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"1051"},{"type":"tags","id":"1052"},{"type":"tags","id":"2082"},{"type":"tags","id":"4632"},{"type":"tags","id":"5608"},{"type":"tags","id":"5611"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"7007"},{"type":"contributions","id":"9069"},{"type":"contributions","id":"26780"},{"type":"contributions","id":"49433"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78421","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/78421"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 56-year-old man has recently undergone an elective inguinal hernia repair under general anaesthesia. The procedure was successful with no intra-operative complications. While in the post-anaesthesia care unit he develops severe postoperative nausea and vomiting. His past medical history is significant for hypertension, hypercholesterolaemia and Parkinson\u2019s disease. He is reviewed by the Anaesthetist who prescribes an anti-emetic. \u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"What is the most suitable choice of anti-emetic for this situation?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Metoclopramide","Prochlorperazine","Dexamethasone","Droperidol","Ondansetron"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMetoclopramide\u003C/strong\u003E, \u003Cstrong\u003EProchlorperazine\u003C/strong\u003E and \u003Cstrong\u003EDroperidol\u003C/strong\u003E all cause some D2 receptor inhibition and can thus cause extrapyramidal side effects and worsen the symptoms of Parkinson\u2019s disease. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDexamethasone\u003C/strong\u003E administered to an awake patient can cause distressing perineal dysaesthesia and as such is avoided in these situations. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E5-HT3 receptor antagonists such as \u003Cstrong\u003EOndansetron\u003C/strong\u003E are the most suitable for this patient due to their concurrent Parkinson\u0027s Disease. Cyclizine and Domperidone (which do not cross the blood-brain barrier to any significant degree) may also be considered in this situation as they are also safe to use in Parkinson\u2019s disease.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Anti-emetics with D2 receptor inhibition can cause extrapyramidal side effects and worsen the symptoms of Parkinson\u0027s Disease.","Ondansetron, a 5-HT3 receptor antagonist, is a suitable anti-emetic for patients with Parkinson\u0027s Disease due to its lack of dopaminergic activity."],"references":["Nicholson G, Pereira AC, Hall GM. Parkinson\u0027s disease and anaesthesia. Br J Anaesth. 2002 Dec;89(6):904-16. doi: 10.1093/bja/aef268. PMID: 12453936. Available from: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/12453936/","Kaur, Jaslovleen, et al. Ondansetron for the treatment of Parkinson\u2019s disease psychosis: Rationale and literature review. Annals of Movement Disorders, 2023, 6.2: 72-78. Available from: https://journals.lww.com/aomd/fulltext/2023/06020/ondansetron_for_the_treatment_of_parkinson_s.3.aspx","Ramprasad C, Douglas JY, Moshiree B. Parkinson\u0027s Disease and Current Treatments for Its Gastrointestinal Neurogastromotility Effects. Curr Treat Options Gastroenterol. 2018 Dec;16(4):489-510. doi: 10.1007/s11938-018-0201-3. PMID: 30361854. Available from: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/30361854/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63783"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12059"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63783","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/63783"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-10T18:23:27+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-10T18:24:05+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"4626"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78421"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"1","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/1"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude34","name":"Anaesthesia","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"5"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"66","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/66"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Management","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"72","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/72"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Graduating","synonyms":null,"description":"Only suitable for a graduating medical student at the end of their deg